name: NAD(P)H-hydrate epimerase
reaction: (1) (6R)-6beta-hydroxy-1,4,5,6-tetrahydronicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide = (6S)-6beta-hydroxy-1,4,5,6-tetrahydronicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide [RN:R10280]; (2) (6R)-6beta-hydroxy-1,4,5,6-tetrahydronicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide phosphate = (6S)-6beta-hydroxy-1,4,5,6-tetrahydronicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide phosphate [RN:R10281]
comment: The enzyme can use either (R)-NADH-hydrate or (R)-NADPH-hydrate as a substrate. Its physiological role is to convert the (R) forms to the (S) forms, which could then be restored to active dinucleotides by EC 4.2.1.93, ATP-dependent NAD(P)H-hydrate dehydratase.

references.title: Extremely conserved ATP- or ADP-dependent enzymatic system for nicotinamide nucleotide repair.
